Hi ENS, nice to meet you 🙂 I would like to integrate ENS into a smart contract. Which is the ENS address? Is it 0x00000000000C2E074eC69A0dFb2997BA6C7d2e1e ? I also found this one 0x57f1887a8BF19b14fC0dF6Fd9B2acc9Af147eA85 . For instance to register a domain I have to interact with the BaseRegistrar, right? Going to the latter address 0x57f18...2e1e I find the following to functions
```
function register(uint256 id, address owner, uint duration) external returns(uint) {
      return _register(id, owner, duration, true);
    }
function registerOnly(uint256 id, address owner, uint duration) external returns(uint) {
      return _register(id, owner, duration, false);
    }
```
Ah I see, the first address is the registrar and the second one is the token address?

So for instance if I want to create a new ens domain I would have to call 
```
function register(uint256 id, address owner, uint duration) virtual external returns(uint);
```
with id being the keccak256 of the name, right? and suppose I would like to set a record of an existing ens domain, I would have to call this function?
```
function setRecord(bytes32 node, address owner, address resolver, uint64 ttl) external;
```
but whould I have to turn the domain name into bytes32 first? And the owner address is clear to me, that's mostly msg.sender, but the resolver address?

this is the function I found in the wrapper, but apparently it refers to subnames:
`
/**
     * @notice Sets the subdomain owner in the registry and then wraps the subdomain
     * @param parentNode Parent namehash of the subdomain
     * @param label Label of the subdomain as a string
     * @param owner New owner in the wrapper
     * @param fuses Initial fuses for the wrapped subdomain
     * @param expiry When the name will expire in seconds since the Unix epoch
     * @return node Namehash of the subdomain
     */
    function setSubnodeOwner(
        bytes32 parentNode,
        string calldata label,
        address owner,
        uint32 fuses,
        uint64 expiry
    ) public onlyTokenOwner(parentNode) returns (bytes32 node) {
        bytes32 labelhash = keccak256(bytes(label));
        node = _makeNode(parentNode, labelhash);
        _checkCanCallSetSubnodeOwner(parentNode, node);
        _checkFusesAreSettable(node, fuses);
        bytes memory name = _saveLabel(parentNode, node, label);
        expiry = _checkParentFusesAndExpiry(parentNode, node, fuses, expiry);
        if (!_isWrapped(node)) {
            ens.setSubnodeOwner(parentNode, labelhash, address(this));
            _wrap(node, name, owner, fuses, expiry);
        } else {
            _updateName(parentNode, node, label, owner, fuses, expiry);
        }
    }`

so the parent node should be .eth right?

