Hey, what library are you using?

Here's a version of the function using ethers.js that should work as intended on goerli (an Ethereum test network):
```js
const getENSData = async () => {
  const provider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider(
    'https://rpc.ankr.com/eth_goerli', // remove the "_goerli" for mainnet
    'goerli' // change to "homestead" for mainnet Ethereum
  )

  try {
    const name = await provider.lookupAddress(owner)
    const avatar = await provider.getAvatar(owner)
    return { name, avatar }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching ENS data:', error)
    return { name: '', avatar: '' }
  }
}
```
It seems the thirdweb URL you were using is not an Ethereum RPC endpoint
